#Upset plots

After calculating the number of peaks for each condition, an Upset Plot was done to verify how much overlap was present in the various conditions. In the paper, this was done using Venn-Diagrams, but as these delimitate the number of conditions that can be compared while still being sufficiently coherent, we opted for Upset Plots.

When comparing the individual rats for the various conditions (here only the GR condition is included in the script), one can notice that there are indeed differences between the rats and only a few peaks overlaps.
